de.must.dataobj
Class DataChangedEvent

java.lang.Object
  de.must.dataobj.DataChangedEvent

public class DataChangedEvent
extends java.lang.Object

Data change event. Used for synchronization of data presentations, e.g. to update a ComboBox when a new entry was added by an administration.

Constructor Detail

DataChangedEvent

public DataChangedEvent(java.lang.String entityName,
                        int mode,
                        int sequenceType,
                        java.lang.Class<?> sender,
                        Identifier identifier)
Constructs a new DataChangedEvent. To prevent repeated change consequences, it may be indicated that more updates on the same entity follow by using mode NOT_THE_LAST_OF_A_SEQUENCE_TYPE

Parameters:
entityName - the name of the entity that was changed
mod - the data change mode which may be INSERTION_MODE, UPDATE_MODE or DELETION_MODE
sequenceType - the sequence type which may be SINGLE_TYPE, NOT_THE_LAST_OF_A_SEQUENCE_TYPE or SUMMARY_TYPE
sender - the class who causes the change event
